<p>Financial records consist of account books (7 volumes and one loose page) which record sales and expenses in the early years of his career.  Some of the ledgers contain specific references and contact information for his models.</p>

<p>Miller's three-volume register of his work in bronze describes 400 pieces and includes standard catalog information, casting history, and some sketches.  A two-volume sculpture register (with reproductions of thumbnail size photographs) is a seemingly comprehensive list of all of his work through 2000.
</p> 
